{
  "stem": "26672.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the biggest game in those, it used to be like-- from a piece of wire, we used to make like a-- and for wheel, take a wheel from the bicycle, and roll it along, and catch it in that piece of wire.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So it shouldn't fall over.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was an, also, um, uh, here you have cricket.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't play cricket.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I played football, tried to play football.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We also had a game, it was a piece of wood, short piece of wood with two ends sharpened down and used to hit it, how far it could-- it would travel, or coins against the, the wall, you know.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They had names.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't remember them.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One-- one particular [? pallent-- ?] [? pallent, ?] used to be called, a piece of wood with the-- with the edges, eh, sharpened down so you could hit it, and have fun-- I used to -- [INAUDIBLE] used to be called [? pallent. ?]",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Boys, mostly.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we-- I didn't play much with the girls.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We very much, uh, of the Orthodox sects, and I don't remember playing with girls, to be honest, even at that young age, yeah.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ryki, was yes-- as far as I know, yes, it was very Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Many, I wouldn't-- yeah, there was one large synagogue, which belonged to the town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then each sect had their own [NON-ENGLISH], yeah.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Quite a few.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know exactly how many but quite a few.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because each offshoot had their own-- the rabbi's offshoot had their own.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if you belong to a [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If you belong to the shoe menders, they had their own synagogue.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The tailors had their own synagogue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So each one had their own, their own little pla-- parish.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
